<paragraph id="470EB874FFF0FFAEFCC3F6EBFB7780F7" blockId="25.[813,1452,509,1014]" pageId="25" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis id="75C56466FFF0FFAEFCC3F6EBFC158117" bold="true" box="[813,917,509,534]" pageId="25" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis id="75C56466FFF0FFAEFCC3F6EBFC0F8117" bold="true" box="[813,911,509,534]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="230">Remarks</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
— The colour pattern of 
<taxonomicName id="80B1C3F7FFF0FFAEFB5AF6E9FABF8117" baseAuthorityName="Jerdon" baseAuthorityYear="1849" box="[1204,1343,511,534]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Hemibagrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis id="75C56466FFF0FFAEFB5AF6E9FABF8117" box="[1204,1343,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="230">H. punctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has often been described as a series of large spots along the lateral line (e.g. Ng &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="2320C585FFF0FFAEFC37F528FBF48157" author="Ferraris, C" box="[985,1140,574,598]" pageId="25" pageNumber="230" pagination="289 - 306" refId="ref68520" refString="Ferraris, C. J., M. A. McGrouther &amp; K. L. Parkinson, 2000. A critical review of the types and putative types of southern Asian marine and freshwater fish species in the Australian Museum named by Francis Day. Records of the Australian Museum, 52: 289 - 306." type="journal article" year="2000">Ferraris, 2000</bibRefCitation>
), but this pattern is based on poorly-preserved material. Photographs of fresh material (
<figureCitation id="DF8AA4F1FFF0FFAEFCDBF568FC0E8197" box="[821,910,638,662]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[114,149,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[113,752,1445,1984]" captionTargetId="figure-444@25.[103,752,1428,1985]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 19. a, Hemibagrus punctatus, ZSI FF 1223, 193.1 mm SL; India: Hemavathy River; b, Specimen (not preserved) from Cauvery River, Karnataka (approx. 250 mm SL) showing live colouration. (Photograph courtesy of Johnny Jensen; copyright www.jjphoto." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351828" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5351828/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="230">Fig. 19b</figureCitation>
) show that 
<taxonomicName id="80B1C3F7FFF0FFAEFBE6F569FB108197" baseAuthorityName="Jerdon" baseAuthorityYear="1849" box="[1032,1168,639,662]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Hemibagrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis id="75C56466FFF0FFAEFBE6F569FB108197" box="[1032,1168,639,662]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="230">H. punctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
actually possesses vertical columns of spots much like 
<taxonomicName id="80B1C3F7FFF0FFAEFB89F589FB5E81B7" box="[1127,1246,671,694]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Mystus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="menoda">
<emphasis id="75C56466FFF0FFAEFB89F589FB5E81B7" box="[1127,1246,671,694]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="230">H. menoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="80B1C3F7FFF0FFAEFAF6F589FA2581B7" box="[1304,1445,671,694]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Hemibagrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="peguensis">
<emphasis id="75C56466FFF0FFAEFAF6F589FA2581B7" box="[1304,1445,671,694]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="230">H. peguensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although the colour patterns of 
<taxonomicName id="80B1C3F7FFF0FFAEFB7AF5A9FA8D81D7" box="[1172,1293,703,726]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Mystus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="menoda">
<emphasis id="75C56466FFF0FFAEFB7AF5A9FA8D81D7" box="[1172,1293,703,726]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="230">H. menoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="80B1C3F7FFF0FFAEFAF0F5A9FA2C81D7" box="[1310,1452,703,726]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Hemibagrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="peguensis">
<emphasis id="75C56466FFF0FFAEFAF0F5A9FA2C81D7" box="[1310,1452,703,726]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="230">H. peguensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="80B1C3F7FFF0FFAEFCB3F5C9FC6A81F7" baseAuthorityName="Jerdon" baseAuthorityYear="1849" box="[861,1002,735,758]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Hemibagrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis id="75C56466FFF0FFAEFCB3F5C9FC6A81F7" box="[861,1002,735,758]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="230">H. punctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very similar in that the sides of the body are marked with a series of vertical columns of black spots, there are slight but distinct differences between 
<taxonomicName id="80B1C3F7FFF0FFAEFA7FF409FC168057" baseAuthorityName="Jerdon" baseAuthorityYear="1849" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Hemibagrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis id="75C56466FFF0FFAEFA7FF409FC168057" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="230">H. punctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the 
<taxonomicName id="80B1C3F7FFF0FFAEFC13F429FBF78057" box="[1021,1143,831,854]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Mystus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="menoda">
<emphasis id="75C56466FFF0FFAEFC13F429FBF78057" box="[1021,1143,831,854]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="230">H. menoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<taxonomicName id="80B1C3F7FFF0FFAEFB47F429FAB78057" baseAuthorityName="Jerdon" baseAuthorityYear="1849" box="[1193,1335,831,854]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Hemibagrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis id="75C56466FFF0FFAEFB47F429FAB78057" box="[1193,1335,831,854]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="230">H. punctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the spots in the middle of the columns along the lateral line remain distinctly larger (at least twice the size of the other spots in the same column) in almost all the columns (save the last one or two) whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="80B1C3F7FFF0FFAEFBCBF4A9FB1980D7" box="[1061,1177,959,982]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bagridae" genus="Mystus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="menoda">
<emphasis id="75C56466FFF0FFAEFBCBF4A9FB1980D7" box="[1061,1177,959,982]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="230">H. menoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, only the spots in the first three or four columns are distinctly larger.
</paragraph>
